Anonymous Mon 02 Apr 2018 01:44:14 No.14918272 Report
Quoted By:
>>14912342
If i’m writing a descriptive bit and adding sensory stuff i use each > as if it were a new sentence

If i’m writing character interactions i use each new > as if it were a cut in a movie or for new dialogue. It allows the story to read a lot snappier than most other literature at the risk of the reader getting a little lost but it works well in some regards

Another thing to think of is how you can use the informal style to present the characters differently such as by directly conveying thoughts that the readers will already understand in the context. Fir example you could describe physically how someone reacts when they know they’re being lied to

His eyebrow raised ever so slightly and a humorless chuckle escaped his lips. He shook his head dismissively before giving a sarcastic nod.
“Sure”

As opposed to simply giving his thought process

>Well that’s a load of shit

The result is far less formal but it’s more focused on how we actually feel when we ourselves are in the situation as the character
